CNi 88
No.55/4/CF-66(i)
- GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
(Department of Cabinet Affairs)
IMMEDIATE
New Delhi, the 14th February, 1966.
The undersigned is directed to state that, with effect
from the forenoon of February 14, 1966,
(i) Shri Jagannath Rao relinquished the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Labour,
Employment & Rehabilitation, and assumed the
office of Minister of State in the Departments
of Parliamentary Affairs and Communications;
(ii) Shri D.R, Chavan relinquished the office of
Deputy Minister of Planning, and assumed the
office of Deputy Minister in the Ministry of
Labour, Employment & Rehabilitation;
(1ii) Shri Shyam Dhar Mishra relinquished the office
of Deputy Minister in the Ministry of Defence,
and assumed the office of Deputy Minister in
the Ministry of Food, Agriculturo, Community
Development & Cooperation; and
(iv) Shri V.C. Shukla relinquished the office of
Deputy Minister in the Departments of
Parliamentary Affairs and Communications,
and assumed the office of Deputy Minister
in the Ministry of Home Affairs.
(D.P. Chopra)
for Cabinet Secretary.
To
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the Prime Minister/the
Private Secretary to the Prime Minister, for information,
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the President/the
Private Secretary to the Vice-President, for information.
Deampra
(D.P. Chopra)
Under Secretary to the. Cabinet.
Copy forwarded to all Secretaries/Special Secretaries/
Additional Secretaried to the Government of India/Chairman,
Railway Board, for information.
Copy forwarded to all Ministries/Departmonts of the
Government of India/Lok Sabha Secretariat/Rajya Sabha
Secretariat, for information.
(D.P. Chopra)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
*Sawhney*
